SIMPLE: now
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Now
<hw>Now</hw> <pr>(nou)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>nou</ets>,
<ets>nu</ets>, AS. <ets>n⟦umac⟧</ets>, <ets>nu</ets>; akin to D., OS., &
OHG. <ets>nu</ets>, G. <ets>nu</ets>, <ets>nun</ets>, Icel.,
<ets>n⟦umac⟧</ets>, Dan., Sw., & Goth. <ets>nu</ets>, L.
<ets>nunc</ets>, Gr. <grk>ny`</grk>, <grk>ny^n</grk>, Skr.
<ets>nu</ets>, <ets>n⟦umac⟧</ets>. ⟦root⟧193. Cf.
<er>New</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>At the present time; at this moment; at the time of
speaking; instantly; <as>as, I will write <ex>now</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have a patient <qex>now</qex> living, at an advanced age, who
discharged blood from his lungs thirty years ago.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Very lately; not long ago.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They that but <qex>now</qex>, for honor and for plate,⟦br⟧
Made the sea blush with blood, resign their hate.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>At a time contemporaneous with something spoken of
or contemplated; at a particular time referred to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ship was <qex>now</qex> in the midst of the sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. xiv. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>In present circumstances; things being as they are;
-- hence, used as a connective particle, to introduce an inference or an
explanation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How shall any man distinguish <qex>now</qex> betwixt a parasite
and a man of honor?</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why should he live, <qex>now</qex> nature bankrupt is?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then cried they all again, saying, Not this man, but Barabbas.
<qex>Now</qex>, Barabbas was a robber.</q> <rj><qau>John xviii.
40.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The other great and undoing mischief which befalls men is, by
their being misrepresented. <qex>Now</qex>, by calling evil good, a man
is misrepresented to others in the way of slander.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Now and again</b></col>, <cd>now and then;
occasionally.</cd> -- <col><b>Now and now</b></col>, <cd>again and
again; repeatedly.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Chaucer.</au> --
<col><b>Now and then</b></col>, <cd>at one time and another;
indefinitely; occasionally; not often; at intervals.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧A mead
here, there a heath, and <xex>now and then</xex> a wood.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Drayton.</au> -- <col><b>Now now</b></col>, <cd>at this very
instant; precisely now.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Why, even
<xex>now now</xex>, at holding up of this finger, and before the turning
down of this.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>J. Webster (1607).</au> -- <col><b>Now . . .
now</b></col>, <cd>alternately; at one time . . . at another time.</cd>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Now</xex> high, <xex>now</xex> low, <xex>now</xex> master
up, <xex>now</xex> miss.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Pope.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Now</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Now
<hw>Now</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Existing at the present time;
present.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Our <xex>now</xex>
happiness.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Now</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Now
<hw>Now</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The present time or moment; the
present.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nothing is there to come, and nothing past;⟦br⟧
But an eternal <qex>now</qex> does ever last.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 985 --></p>

<p><ent>Nowadays</ent>⟦br⟧
